The Boksburg SPCA is in urgent need of dog food at the moment, owing to the increased number of animals taken in on a daily basis, Boksburg Advertiser reports.
Members of the public can assist the Boksburg SPCA by donating dry dog food (adult and puppy) and canned dog food (adult and puppy).
READ MORE: Litres galore for SPCA animals
Any donations can be dropped off at the society during office hours from 8.30am to 4pm weekly or 8.30am to noon on Saturdays.
You can also call the Boksburg SPCA office on 011 916 5906/7 for a driver to come and collect anywhere in Boksburg.
